
Some benchmark cases that have been set up in CLUBB.

arm:          Shallow cumulus over the ARM site in Oklahoma.
              http://appconv.metoffice.com/blclouds/GCSS_BLclouds_files/Past_cases.html#case7
              Brown et al., 2002:  Large-eddy simulation 
              of the diurnal cycle of shallow cumulus convection over land. 
              Quart. J. Roy. Meteor.  Soc., 128, 1075-1093. 

astex:        Shallow Cu rising into Sc over the Northern Altantic.
              http://appconv.metoffice.com/blclouds/GCSS_BLclouds_files/Past_cases.html#case3
              Bretherton, C. S., S. K. Krueger, M. C. Wyant, P. Bechtold, E. van Meijgaard, 
              B. Stevens, and J. Teixeira, 1999: A GCSS boundary layer model intercomparison 
              study of the first ASTEX Lagrangian experiment. Bound.-Layer Meteor., 93, 341-380. 

atex:         Trade-wind Cu under a strong inversion.
              http://appconv.metoffice.com/blclouds/GCSS_BLclouds_files/Past_cases.html#case6
              B. Stevens et al., 2000: Simulations of trade-wind cumuli under a strong inversion, 
              J. Atmos. Sci, 58,1870-1891. 

bomex:        Trade-wind non-precipitating Cu.
              http://appconv.metoffice.com/blclouds/GCSS_BLclouds_files/Past_cases.html#case5
              Siebesma, A. P., and coauthors, 2003: A large-eddy simulation intercomparison 
              study of shallow cumulus convection. J. Atmos. Sci., 60, 1201-1219.

dycoms2_rf01: Marine Sc under a strong inversion.
              http://appconv.metoffice.com/blclouds/GCSS_BLclouds_files/Past_cases.html#case9
              Stevens, B., and coauthors, 2005: Observations of nocturnal marine 
              stratocumulus as represented by large eddy simulation. 
              Mon. Wea. Rev., 133, 1443-1462.

dycoms2_rf02: Drizzling marine Sc.
              http://appconv.metoffice.com/blclouds/GCSS_BLclouds_files/Past_cases.html#case10
              Wyant,M.C. and coauthors, 2007: A single-column model intercomparison 
              of a heavily drizzling stratocumulus-topped boundary layer, 
              J. Geophys. Res., 112, D24204, doi:10.1029/2007JD008536. 

fire:         Marine Sc.
              http://appconv.metoffice.com/blclouds/GCSS_BLclouds_files/Past_cases.html#case1
              Bechtold, P., and coauthors, 1996: Modeling a stratocumulus-topped PBL: 
              Intercomparisons among different 1D codes and with LES. 
              Bull. Amer. Meteor. Soc., 77, 2033-2042.

gabls2:       Diurnal cycle of boundary layer over land, including
              stable nighttime layer.
              http://www.misu.su.se/~gunilla/gabls/

mpace_a:      Multi-layered, mixed-phase Arctic stratus.
              http://science.arm.gov/workinggroup/cpm/scm/scmic5/index.html

mpace_b:      Single-layered, mixed-phase Arctic stratus.
              http://science.arm.gov/workinggroup/cpm/scm/scmic5/index.html
              
rico:         Precipitating Shallow Cumulus Case
              http://www.knmi.nl/samenw/rico/index.html

wangara:      Dry convective boundary layer over land.
              2002: "A PDF-based model for boundary layer clouds. 
              Part II: Model results." J.-C. Golaz,
              V. E. Larson, and W. R. Cotton. 
              J. Atmos. Sci., 59, 3552.3571.        

